   "source": [
    "# 🧬 DrugDiscovery.ai — AI-Powered Drug Repurposing Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "**Demonstration for UGA Institute for AI — Drug Research & Development Certificate**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates an end-to-end AI pipeline for identifying and evaluating drug repurposing candidates. It combines:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Literature Mining** — RAG over recent arXiv papers\n",
    "2. **Molecular Property Analysis** — ADMET properties from PubChem\n",
    "3. **LLM Reasoning** — Structured evaluation of candidates\n",
    "4. **Report Generation** — Professional HTML output\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Author:** Amanda Kavner, PhD  \n",
    "**Target Disease:** Alzheimer's Disease (configurable)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n",
    "# Setup & Imports\n",
    "# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n",
    "\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, str(Path.cwd() / \"src\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "\n",
    "# Our modules\n",
    "from literature_mining import run_literature_mining, extract_drugs_from_text\n",
    "from molecular_analysis import run_molecular_analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ All modules loaded successfully\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Phase 1: Literature Mining & RAG\n",
    "\n",
    "Search arXiv for recent papers on drug repurposing for the target disease. Extract key findings, drug mentions, and build a knowledge base."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n",
    "# Configuration\n",
    "# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n",
    "\n",
    "DISEASE = \"Alzheimer's disease\"\n",
    "MAX_PAPERS = 15\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Target disease: {DISEASE}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Max papers: {MAX_PAPERS}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run literature mining\n",
    "kb = run_literature_mining(DISEASE, max_results=MAX_PAPERS)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Display top drug mentions from literature\n",
    "print(\"\\n💊 Drugs mentioned in literature (ranked by frequency):\\n\")\n",
    "for drug, info in list(kb['drug_mentions'].items())[:15]:\n",
    "    print(f\"  {drug:25s} — {info['count']} paper(s)\")\n",
    "    for arxiv_id in info['papers'][:2]:\n",
    "        paper = next((p for p in kb['papers'] if p['arxiv_id'] == arxiv_id), None)\n",
    "        if paper:\n",
    "            print(f\"    └─ {paper['title'][:80]}...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Display sample key findings\n",
    "print(\"\\n🔬 Sample Key Findings from Literature:\\n\")\n",
    "for i, finding in enumerate(kb['all_findings'][:8]):\n",
    "    print(f\"  {i+1}. {finding[:150]}...\")\n",
    "    print()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Phase 2: Molecular Property Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Fetch molecular properties from PubChem for the top repurposing candidates identified in the literature. Compare against approved drugs for the target disease."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n",
    "# Select candidates from literature + known repurposing candidates\n",
    "# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n",
    "\n",
    "# Top drugs from literature mining\n",
    "literature_drugs = list(kb['drug_mentions'].keys())[:8]\n",
    "print(f\"Drugs from literature: {literature_drugs}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Known repurposing candidates for Alzheimer's (from prior research)\n",
    "known_candidates = [\"metformin\", \"rapamycin\", \"lithium\", \"naltrexone\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Approved Alzheimer's drugs for comparison\n",
    "approved_drugs = [\"donepezil\", \"rivastigmine\", \"galantamine\", \"memantine\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Merge and deduplicate\n",
    "all_candidates = list(set([d.lower() for d in literature_drugs + known_candidates]))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nRepurposing candidates: {all_candidates}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Approved drugs (comparison): {approved_drugs}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run molecular property analysis\n",
    "df = run_molecular_analysis(\n",
    "    candidate_drugs=all_candidates,\n",
    "    disease=DISEASE,\n",
    "    approved_drugs=approved_drugs,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Display the full property table\n",
    "print(\"\\n📋 Full Molecular Property Table:\\n\")\n",
    "display_cols = [\"name\", \"molecular_formula\", \"molecular_weight\", \"log_p\",\n",
    "                 \"h_bond_donors\", \"h_bond_acceptors\", \"tpsa\",\n",
    "                 \"lipinski_violations\", \"drug_like\", \"status\"]\n",
    "print(df[display_cols].to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Summary statistics\n",
    "print(\"\\n📊 Summary Statistics:\\n\")\n",
    "candidates = df[df['status'] == 'repurposing_candidate']\n",
    "approved = df[df['status'] == 'approved_drug']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Repurposing candidates: {len(candidates)}\")\n",
    print(f\"  Drug-like (Lipinski): {candidates['drug_like'].sum()}/{len(candidates)}\")\n",
    print(f\"  Avg MW: {candidates['molecular_weight'].mean():.1f} Da\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Avg LogP: {candidates['log_p'].mean():.2f}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(f\"Approved drugs: {len(approved)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Drug-like (Lipinski): {approved['drug_like'].sum()}/{len(approved)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Avg MW: {approved['molecular_weight'].mean():.1f} Da\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Avg LogP: {approved['log_p'].mean():.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Display generated plots\n",
    "from IPython.display import Image, display\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "output_dir = Path(\"output\")\n",
    "for img in sorted(output_dir.glob(\"*.png\")):\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n📊 {img.name}\")\n",
    "    display(Image(filename=str(img)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Phase 3: LLM Reasoning Engine (Preview)\n",
    "\n",
    "The following demonstrates the structured output format for the LLM reasoning module. In the full pipeline, this uses the knowledge base + molecular properties as context."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Prepare context for LLM reasoning\n",
    "llm_context = {\n",
    "    \"disease\": DISEASE,\n",
    "    \"literature_summary\": {\n",
    "        \"total_papers\": kb[\"total_papers\"],\n",
    "        \"top_drugs\": {k: v[\"count\"] for k, v in list(kb[\"drug_mentions\"].items())[:10]},\n",
    "        \"key_findings\": kb[\"all_findings\"][:5],\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"molecular_data\": df[[\"name\", \"molecular_weight\", \"log_p\", \"drug_like\", \"status\"]].to_dict(orient=\"records\"),\n",
    "    \"top_candidates\": df[df[\"status\"] == \"repurposing_candidate\"].sort_values(\"drug_like\", ascending=False)[\"name\"].tolist()[:5],\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"📦 LLM Context prepared:\")\n",
    "print(json.dumps(llm_context, indent=2, default=str)[:2000])\n",
    "print(\"\\n... (truncated)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrated:\n",
    "\n",
    "- ✅ **Literature RAG**: Automated search and extraction from arXiv\n",
    "- ✅ **Molecular Analysis**: Real-time PubChem data with Lipinski evaluation\n",
    "- ✅ **Comparative Visualization**: Candidates vs. approved drugs\n",
    "- ✅ **Structured Data Pipeline**: Ready for LLM reasoning module\n",
    "\n",
    "**Next steps (Phase 3+4):** Wire up the LLM reasoning engine with structured output constraints and generate the final HTML report."
   ]
  }
